The centre benefits from excellent accessibility, being only 550m* by road from the Bruce Highway on and off ramps, and an abundance of on-grade car parking for some 294* vehicles (3.18* bays per 100sqm of GLA).

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located in the heart of the burgeoning Brisbane to Gold Coast growth corridor, Home Focus Pimpama will be one of the largest mixed-use homemaker centres in Queensland and the epicentre for large format retail shopping in the Northern Gold Coast Region.

The first stage of this exciting new development is already underway and comprises approx. 28,000sqm of floorspace which is approx. 60% pre-committed to major national retailers including (STCA) Bunnings Warehouse, BP Australia, Wild Bean Café, Guzman y Gomez and a 24/7 gym which will act as key customer attractors and traffic generators for the site.  Upon completion of all proposed stages, Home Focus Pimpama will have a total floor area of approx. 53,000sqm. 

The centre is being built on an exceptionally high-profile site with an approx. 630m frontage to Yawalpah Road, just off Exit 49 of the Pacific Motorway (M1), which provides outstanding accessibility from an expansive and fast growing trade area.  Convenient multi-directional access will be provided through two intersections on Yawalpah Road and a third intersection on the Old Pacific Highway.  The M1 runs along the rear boundary of the site for approx. 1km with approx. 54 million vehicles annually. 

The already substantial main trade area population is projected to increase at an average annual growth rate of approx. 2.5% – significantly higher than the projected rate for South East Queensland (2018 to 2036).  The primary trade area also generally consists of a younger, family based population that earn higher than average household incomes – ideal for large format retail spending.

Home Focus Pimpama is well designed over a single level, fronting onto a significant provision of at-grade car parking with large signage allocations and the ability for retailers to brand the façades in their corporate livery (STCA).  Flexible showrooms areas are available for lease from approx. 400sqm to 4,000sqm and greater.  In addition to large format retail, there are opportunities for café / food & beverage operators, drive-thru quick service retail, medical / allied health businesses and more.

Do not miss this opportunity to join Bunnings Warehouse and secure a prime position in Queensland’s most exciting large format retail development currently underway.  For more information on Home Focus Pimpama, please contact exclusive CBRE leasing agents Andrew Brimson and Sam Macgregor.
